cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as it proposes a neural network-based denoiser for noisy data. It also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it assumes known noisy channel densities and aims to optimize the denoising performance. Multimedia (cs.MM) is also a possible sub-category as the denoiser can be applied to various types of data, including images and videos. Finally, neural networks (cs.NE) is another possible sub-category as the proposed algorithm is based on a neural network architecture.
